action of these galaxies in the form of satellites in massive halos. Our\nclustering measurements on scales below $0.4\\,h^{-1}{\\rm {Mpc}}$ allow us to\nstudy the small-scale spatial distribution of satellites inside halos. While\nthe clustering of luminosity-threshold samples can be well described by a\nNavarro-Frenk-White (NFW) profile, that of the reddest galaxies prefers a\nsteeper or more concentrated profile. Finally, we also use galaxy samples of\nconstant number density at different redshifts to study the evolution of\nluminous galaxies, and find the clustering to be consistent with passive\nevolution in the redshift range of $0.5 \\lesssim z \\lesssim 0.6$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Jan 2014 21:06:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 7 May 2014 03:55:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-08-12"}
