{"id":"1401.3135","submitter":"Josip Globevnik","authors":"Josip Globevnik","title":"A complete complex hypersurface in the ball of C^N","comments":"23 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CV","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In 1977 P.Yang asked whether there exist complete immersed complex\nsubmanifolds g : M^k --> C^N with bounded image. A positive answer is known for\nholomorphic curves (k=1) and partial answers are known for the case when k>1.\nThe principal result of the present paper is a construction of a holomorphic\nfunction on the open unit ball B_N of C^N whose real part is unbounded on every\npath in B_N of finite length that ends on the boundary of B_N. A consequence is\nthe existence of a complete, closed, complex hypersurface in B_N. This gives a\npositive answer to Yang's question in all dimensions k, N, 1\\leq k<N, by\nproviding properly embedded complete complex manifolds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Jan 2014 10:50:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-01-15"}
